  "authors": ["Synthetic Author A", "Synthetic Author B"],
  "abstract": "This supplement provides the complete derivation of the two-sector response kernel R_ij = C_0 delta_ij + C_2 I_ij from the defining radial momentum integral. We decompose the kernel into scalar+longitudinal (Sector A) and transverse (Sector B) components, apply a product-rule reorganization, project onto basis tensors, integrate analytically, and verify numerically. The epsilon -> 0 limiting case is analyzed, showing the expected isotropic reduction in d = 2. All 96 intermediate terms are provided as an electronic artifact for machine reproducibility.",
